:::summary
Angels — the heavenly messengers and ministers of God — appear throughout Scripture from Genesis to Revelation, serving as heralds of divine communication, agents of divine judgment, guardians of God's people, and worshippers before the throne of the Almighty. From the cherubim guarding Eden to the seraphim of Isaiah's vision, from the angel Gabriel's annunciation to Mary to the Apostle John's apocalyptic visions, angels are a persistent and glorious testimony to the reality of the spiritual world and the active presence of God in human affairs.
